  <h1>Common Questions</h1>
  <p class="question">Does Promptly cost clients money?<p>
	<p class="answer">Sometimes. While Promptly is a free service, it may cost clients a few cents to receive each text message, depending on their service plan.</p>

	<p class="question">How can clients unsubscribe?</p>
	<p class="answer">Clients can unsubscribe by replying STOP to any text message.</p>

	<p class="question">What about privacy? Are text messages confidential?</p>
	<p class="answer">No. Text messages are not confidential. For example, the City and County of San Francisco will not send any messages to clients without their </p>explicit permission. <%= link_to "Here is an example of an agreement form", controller: "pages", action: "documents" %> San Franciscans are given in order to consent to receive text messages.

	<p class="question">What phone number will text messages come from?</p>
	<p class="answer">Promptly uses a third-party vendor to send messages. You will need to buy a phone number from a vendor. <% link_to "Twilio", "http://www.twilio.com" %> has more information on their site.</p>

	<p class="question">What if a client's phone is disconnected?</p>
	<p class="answer">The client will stop receiving text messages.</p>

	<p class="question">What languages are available?</p>
	<p class="answer">Promptly can support text messages in any language the third-party vendor supports.</p>

